---
const title = "Eqho | Free Offline Voice-to-Text Dictation";
const description = "Speak anywhere Windows lets you type. Powered by OpenAI's Whisper, running 100% locally on your machine with zero cloud dependency.";
const author = "Daniel Mevit";
const year = 2026; 
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <meta name="keywords" content="speech to text, voice to text, dictation software, offline speech recognition, free dictation app, voice typing for Windows, OpenAI Whisper app, faster-whisper GUI, private speech to text, local voice recognition, no-cloud transcription" />
    <meta name="author" content={author} />

    <!-- Inter Font -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <!-- Open Graph for Link Sharing -->
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://danielmevit.github.io/Eqho/" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/Eqho/main/logo/logo_horizontal_dark.png" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Eqho" />

    <style>
      :root {
        /* GitHub Dark Theme Palette */
        --color-bg: #0d1117;
        --color-card-bg: #161b22;
        --color-text: #c9d1d9;
        --color-heading: #ffffff;
        --color-blue: #58a6ff;
        --color-muted: #8b949e;
        --color-border: #30363d;
        --color-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
        --color-hover: #1f242c;
      }

      body {
        font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        background-color: var(--color-bg);
        color: var(--color-text);
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }

      main {
        max-width: 960px;
        margin: 8rem auto;
        padding: 0 2rem;
      }

      h1, h2, h3 {
        color: var(--color-heading);
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 3.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        margin: 0;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 2rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        margin-top: 5rem;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }

      h3 {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        margin-top: 3rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        color: var(--color-blue);
      }

      p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

      ul { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
      li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

      a {
        color: var(--color-blue);
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      /* Logo and Header Styling */
      header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 6rem;
      }

      .header-title-container {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      }

      .logo-link {
        display: flex;
      }

      .logo-img {
        width: 160px; 
        height: auto;
      }

      .header-desc {
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        color: var(--color-muted);
        max-width: 680px;
        margin: 0 auto 1.5rem auto;
      }

      section { margin-bottom: 6rem; }

      /* Visual Showcase */
      .visual-comparison {
        margin: 4rem 0;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .visual-comparison img {
        max-width: 100%;
        border-radius: 8px;
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        box-shadow: 0 12px 24px var(--color-shadow);
      }

      .visual-caption {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--color-muted);
      }

      /* Grid for Features */
      .grid-3 {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
        margin-top: 3rem;
      }

      .grid-card {
        background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 2rem;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 12px var(--color-shadow);
      }

      .grid-card h3 { 
        margin-top: 0; 
        color: var(--color-heading); 
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      /* FAQ Accordion Styling */
      .faq-container {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1rem;
        margin-top: 2rem;
      }

      .faq-item {
        background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow: hidden;
        transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
      }
      
      .faq-item:hover {
        background-color: var(--color-hover);
      }

      .faq-item summary {
        padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        color: var(--color-heading);
        cursor: pointer;
        list-style: none;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        user-select: none;
      }

      .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

      .faq-item summary::after {
        content: '+';
        color: var(--color-blue);
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        line-height: 1;
        font-weight: 400;
      }

      .faq-item[open] summary {
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
      }

      .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '−'; }

      .faq-content {
        padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
        color: var(--color-text);
        background-color: var(--color-bg);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
      }

      .faq-content p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

      /* Code Block & Copy Button Styling */
      .code-wrapper {
        position: relative;
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
      }

      pre {
        background-color: var(--color-card-bg);
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        color: var(--color-text);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        padding-top: 2.5rem;
        border-radius: 8px;
        overflow-x: auto;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        margin: 0;
      }

      .copy-button {
        position: absolute;
        top: 0.5rem;
        right: 0.5rem;
        background-color: transparent;
        border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        color: var(--color-muted);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 0.4rem;
        cursor: pointer;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        transition: all 0.2s ease;
      }

      .copy-button:hover {
        background-color: var(--color-hover);
        color: var(--color-text);
        border-color: var(--color-muted);
      }

      .copy-button svg {
        width: 16px;
        height: 16px;
        fill: currentColor;
      }

      code { 
        font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, SF Mono, Menlo, Consolas, Liberation Mono, monospace; 
      }
      
      p code, li code {
        background-color: rgba(110, 118, 129, 0.4);
        padding: 0.2em 0.4em;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-size: 0.85em;
      }

      footer {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 8rem;
        padding: 4rem 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
        color: var(--color-muted);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <header>
        <div class="header-title-container">
          <a href="https://github.com/danielmevit/eqho" class="logo-link">
            <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/Eqho/main/logo/logo_horizontal_dark.png" alt="Eqho logo" class="logo-img" />
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="header-desc">
          Speak anywhere Windows lets you type. Powered by OpenAI's Whisper, running 100% locally on your machine with zero cloud dependency.
        </p>

        <div class="visual-comparison">
          <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DanielMevit/Eqho/main/assets/eqho_app_screenshot.webp" alt="Eqho dashboard dark theme screenshot, showing the live transcription overlay and local settings dashboard" />
          <p class="visual-caption">Eqho features a clean dark theme, adjustable live transcription overlay, and completely local settings dashboard.</p>
        </div>

        <p>
          <a href="https://github.com/danielmevit/eqho">View Repository on GitHub</a>
        </p>
      </header>

      <section aria-labelledby="features">
        <h2 id="features">Core Features</h2>
        
        <div class="grid-3">
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Private by Design 🔒</h3>
            <p>No cloud, no accounts, no API keys required. Your voice data never leaves your computer. Settings and history remain strictly local.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Lightning Fast ⚡</h3>
            <p>GPU-accelerated through NVIDIA CUDA with automatic CPU fallback. Enjoy a real-time transcription preview as you speak.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Universal Support 🌍</h3>
            <p>Inject text into any focused application—Word, Slack, or IDEs. Features 13 supported languages with one-click model swapping.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Custom Vocabulary</h3>
            <p>Teach the model your specific names, industry jargon, and acronyms to ensure perfect transcription for technical work.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Smart Voice Commands</h3>
            <p>Opt-in formatting commands allow you to say things like "new line", "period", or "delete that" for completely hands-free control.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="grid-card">
            <h3>Hallucination Filtering</h3>
            <p>Fixes the known Whisper quirk where silence is transcribed as "Thank you." Eqho intelligently drops empty audio chunks.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="how-it-works">
        <h2 id="how-it-works">How It Works</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Click into any application where you want to type.</li>
          <li>Press <strong>Alt+Q</strong> (or your custom hotkey). A floating bar will show "Listening…".</li>
          <li>Speak naturally and watch the live transcription preview.</li>
          <li>Press <strong>Alt+Q</strong> again—your words are instantly typed into the active app.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="install">
        <h2 id="install">Installation</h2>
        
        <h3>Windows (Recommended)</h3>
        <p>Grab the <code>Eqho-Setup-&lt;version&gt;.exe</code> from the <strong><a href="https://github.com/danielmevit/eqho/releases">Releases page</a></strong>, double-click, and you are done. Prefer no installer? Use the portable <code>.zip</code>.</p>
        
        <h3>Build From Source (Python)</h3>
        <p>Requires Python 3.10+. The first run will automatically download the default speech model (distil-large-v3, ~1.5 GB).</p>
        
        <div class="code-wrapper">
          <button class="copy-button" aria-label="Copy code">
            <svg class="copy-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M0 6.75C0 5.784.784 5 1.75 5h1.5a.75.75 0 010 1.5h-1.5a.25.25 0 00-.25.25v7.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 00.25-.25v-1.5a.75.75 0 011.5 0v1.5A1.75 1.75 0 019.25 16h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 010 14.25v-7.5z"></path><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5 1.75C5 .784 5.784 0 6.75 0h7.5C15.216 0 16 .784 16 1.75v7.5A1.75 1.75 0 0114.25 11h-7.5A1.75 1.75 0 015 9.25v-7.5zm1.75-.25a.25.25 0 00-.25.25v7.5c0 .138.112.25.25.25h7.5a.25.25 0 00.25-.25v-7.5a.25.25 0 00-.25-.25h-7.5z"></path></svg>
            <svg class="check-icon" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" aria-hidden="true" style="display: none; color: #3fb950;"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M13.78 4.22a.75.75 0 010 1.06l-7.25 7.25a.75.75 0 01-1.06 0L2.22 9.28a.75.75 0 011.06-1.06L6 10.94l6.72-6.72a.75.75 0 011.06 0z"></path></svg>
          </button>
<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/danielmevit/eqho.git
cd Eqho
python -m venv venv && venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python run.py</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section aria-labelledby="faq">
        <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        
        <div class="faq-container">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Is my audio uploaded anywhere?</summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>No. Transcription runs locally via CTranslate2. The only network access required is a one-time download for the AI model you choose to use.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Does it cost anything?</summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>No. Eqho is free, open-source, and has no premium tiers, subscriptions, or word limits.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How accurate is the transcription?</summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>It utilizes Whisper-class accuracy, which is the current state of the art for open speech recognition. You can easily pick a larger model from the settings for tougher audio environments.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
          
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Where are my settings and history saved?</summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              <p>Settings persist in your local user config folder (<code>%APPDATA%\Eqho</code> on Windows). Your data is completely under your control and never touches the cloud.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>
      
    </main>
    
    <footer>
      <p>&copy; {year} {author}. Eqho is licensed under the <a href="https://github.com/danielmevit/eqho/blob/main/LICENSE">GNU AGPL-3.0 License</a>.</p>
      <p>Keywords: speech to text, voice typing, OpenAI Whisper, offline dictation.</p>
    </footer>

    <!-- Script to handle Copy to Clipboard -->
    <script is:inline>
      document.querySelectorAll('.code-wrapper').forEach(wrapper => {
        const button = wrapper.querySelector('.copy-button');
        const code = wrapper.querySelector('code');
        const copyIcon = button.querySelector('.copy-icon');
        const checkIcon = button.querySelector('.check-icon');

        button.addEventListener('click', async () => {
          try {
            await navigator.clipboard.writeText(code.innerText);
            
            // Swap icons
            copyIcon.style.display = 'none';
            checkIcon.style.display = 'block';
            
            // Revert after 2 seconds
            setTimeout(() => {
              copyIcon.style.display = 'block';
              checkIcon.style.display = 'none';
            }, 2000);
          } catch (err) {
            console.error('Failed to copy text: ', err);
          }
        });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
